{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"bold-coach-quail","description":"## What\nThe plan-review gate runs FOUR passes (find → verify → decide → coach; see `passes.py`), but several\nsurfaces describe the whole gate as a \"three-pass (find → verify → decide) advisory coaching review\",\nundercounting the Pass-4 coach. Correct the gate-level descriptions to four-pass.\n\n## Scope (gate-level descriptions — fix)\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py:1` headline\n- `src/rebar/mcp_server.py:657` (review_plan docstring)\n- `src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py:215,225` (CLI help)\n- `src/rebar/schemas/plan_review_verdict.schema.json:5` (schema description)\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:10,48`, `attest.py:13`\n- `docs/plan-review-gate.md` (header + body \"the three passes\" labels)\n\n## Out of scope (preserve)\n- The \"shared three-pass framework (epic 9da1)\" lineage — that framework IS three-pass and is shared.\n- The reviewer prompt `.md` files (`plan_review_finder.md`/`plan_review_verifier.md`) — they name the\n  decision core, and editing them risks the prompt-index drift gate.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] All gate-level \"three-pass\" descriptions read \"four-pass (find → verify → decide → coach)\".\n- [ ] The shared-three-pass-framework (epic 9da1) lineage reference is preserved.\n- [ ] No reviewer prompt `.md` front-matter is changed (drift gate untouched).\n- [ ] `make lint` + test suite pass.","id":"5dd2-e4a6-4189-486d","parent_id":"","priority":3,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Docs: correct mislabeled 'three-pass' plan-review references to four-pass (find->verify->decide->coach)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782343748462820001,"uuid":"fe5bd295-c864-42c9-9ff0-a28232e212f7"}